  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A controlled-experiment verification requirement (Req-HemoVal-01) is declared for the hemolysis validation activity. The supporting validation evidence was gathered through a prospective observational study of patients implanted with the FDA generic centrifugal pump, collecting in-vivo plasma free haemoglobin (PFH) time-series data across five flow-speed operating points. The observational dataset is rich — 47 patients, 1,240 PFH measurements, covering the full clinical operating envelope — and the narrative treats it as functionally equivalent to the controlled bench experiment required by Req-HemoVal-01. Reviewers relying on the narrative description alone would find the evidence compelling; the structured activityType field, however, records 'observational-study' rather than the 'controlled-experiment' mandated by the Requirement, breaking the inference link required for W-AR-03 detection. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; seven fall below required levels, consistent with the MRL 5 gap pattern of the base COU. Decision: Accepted (adversarial — the weakener is deliberately suppressed from hasWeakener to test detector sensitivity).",
