      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-pfh-observational-primary",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Primary hemolysis validation — prospective observational PFH comparison",
      "description": "CFD-predicted hemolysis index values at five operating points (3 L/min/3000 rpm, 4 L/min/3000 rpm, 4 L/min/3500 rpm, 5 L/min/3500 rpm, 5 L/min/4000 rpm) were compared against plasma free haemoglobin measurements collected prospectively from 47 VAD patients over 90-day follow-up periods. Mean absolute error across operating points was 0.031 mg/dL (normalised), within the 0.05 mg/dL acceptance band specified in the credibility plan. The observational cohort covered the full clinical operating envelope and provided statistically adequate sample sizes at each operating point (n ≥ 8). Investigators note that patient-to-patient physiological variability introduces uncontrolled confounders not present in a bench controlled-experiment, but argue that the large cohort size and stratified analysis mitigate this limitation sufficiently for regulatory submission. The validation narrative explicitly cross-references Req-HemoVal-01 and characterises the study as fulfilling its intent.",
